        <title>Diving Into Mathematical Practice 2</title>
        <contents>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;MP&amp;nbsp;2 is about reasoning abstractly and quantitatively. This means that learners can&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;make sense of quantities and their relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;decontextualize situations that use quantities by representing those quantities and their relationships using mathematical symbols.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;contextualize by connecting symbols to their meaning in the problem context.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;Watch the following CCRS Mathematical Practice&amp;nbsp;2 video from the ATLAS program (Hamline University and the Minnesota Numeracy Initiative). It provides clear explanations and examples of decontextualizing and contextualizing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/6jaQ1fEv6ts?end=630" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen=""&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: center; margin:0px 100px 0px 100px;"&gt;Used with permission from ATLAS, ABE Teaching &amp;amp; Learning Advancement System. ATLAS is solely funded by a grant from the Minnesota Department of Education and is housed at Hamline University in St.&amp;nbsp;Paul, Minnesota. Contact information: Dr.&amp;nbsp;Patsy
    Egan, ATLAS Director, &lt;a href="mailto:pegan02@hamline.edu" target="_blank"&gt;pegan02@hamline.edu&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="http://www.atlasABE.org" target="_blank" title="ATLAS website - opens in a new window"&gt;www.atlasABE.org&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You must reach the end of the lesson to receive confirmation of completion.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;Click NEXT to continue.&lt;/p&gt;</contents>
