        <title>Mathematical Practice 2 as a Teacher</title>
        <contents>&lt;h3&gt;Mathematical Practice 2 as a Teacher&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;Next, you will be looking at student work on the Best Buy Tickets task.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Read through all of the solutions in the handout &lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Best%20Buy%20Tickets%20-%20Student%20Work.pdf?time=1688697581459" target="_blank" title="PDF - opens in a new window"&gt;Best Buy Tickets - Student Work&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;Select one to examine more closely.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;li&gt;As you look at that student’s work, answer the following questions in the text box below:
        &lt;ul style="padding-top: 10px;"&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;What evidence can you find of the student making sense of quantities and their relationships?&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;What evidence can you find of the student decontextualizing by representing the situation with symbols?&lt;/li&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;What evidence can you find of the student contextualizing by connecting symbols to their meaning in the problem context?&lt;/li&gt;
        &lt;/ul&gt;
    &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;</contents>
